========,1,preface.
This is a list of kings and queens of the Kingdom and Crown of Castile.
For their predecessors, see List of Castilian counts.
========,2,Kings of Castile.
========,3,Claimants as King of Castile and Léon.
John of Gaunt a great great grandson of Ferdinand III of Castile claimed the title of King of Castile and Léon by virtue of his marriage to Constance, daughter of Peter of Castile.
He conducted several military actions, borrowing heavily from London merchants, to solidify his title, without success.
========,3,House of Trastámara.
Henry II was the illegitimate son of Alfonso XI.
He was made count of Trastámara.
